Definition: feeling or expressing regret or sorrow or a sense of loss over something done or undone
Example: felt regretful over his vanished youth; regretful over mistakes she had made; he felt bad about breaking the vase
Synonyms: UNREGRETFUL, sorry, bad, PENITENT, feeling, or, expressing, regret, sorrow, a, sense, of, loss, over, something, done, undone, felt, regretful, his, vanished, youth, mistakes, she, had, made, he, about, breaking, the, vase
Category: adj.all
